We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The symptoms described are classic for carpal tunnel syndrome, which affects the median nerve. This is a common condition in pregnant women due to fluid retention and weight gain. Ulnar nerve and radial nerve are not commonly involved in carpal tunnel syndrome, and anterior interosseous nerve is a branch of the median nerve.
